# Consult `docs/` for packages in this repo

Before implementing or refactoring code that depends on a library or CLI present in this project’s manifest (for example `package.json`), **start from `docs/README.md`**, then read the linked digest for that dependency. If no note exists yet for that package, skim official upstream documentation and add a concise digest under `docs/` when the knowledge will be reused.

This applies when adding imports, configuring tools, or changing APIs tied to those packages.
